"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856039","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-12","<p>No assessment has been made of the merits of allowing orthoptists to sign hospital eye service spectacle prescriptions. The Opticians Act 1989 sets out who may carry out a sight test and sign a spectacle prescription form. This is restricted under the Act to optometrists registered with the General Optical Council and Ophthalmic Medical Practitioners registered with the General Medical Council.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-03-12T17:06:08.3Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856039/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856039/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856039/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-06","Spectacles: Prescriptions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of allowing orthoptists to sign hospital eye service spectacle prescriptions in order to improve and streamline eye care.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","131205"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856040","Department for Transport","false","2018-03-12","<p>The proportion of trains which did not meet their Public Performance Measure (PPM) on the South-eastern network for the last five years, is as follows:</p><p> </p><p>6 Jan 2013 - 4 Jan 2014 10.3%</p><p>5 Jan 2014 - 3 Jan 2015 11.9%</p><p>4 Jan 2015 - 9 Jan 2016 11.7%</p><p>10 Jan 2016 - 7 Jan 2017 14.1%</p><p>8 Jan 2017 - 6 Jan 2018 11.3%</p><p> </p><p>The responsibility for these was apportioned as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Network Rail</p></td><td><p>Southeastern</p></td><td><p>Other Operators</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>6 Jan 2013 - 4 Jan 2014</p></td><td><p>61%</p></td><td><p>33%</p></td><td><p>6%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>5 Jan 2014 - 3 Jan 2015</p></td><td><p>62%</p></td><td><p>32%</p></td><td><p>6%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>4 Jan 2015 - 9 Jan 2016</p></td><td><p>57%</p></td><td><p>38%</p></td><td><p>5%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>10 Jan 2016 - 7 Jan 2017</p></td><td><p>67%</p></td><td><p>29%</p></td><td><p>4%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>8 Jan 2017 - 6 Jan 2018</p></td><td><p>64%</p></td><td><p>31%</p></td><td><p>5%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>(PPM – defined as services 5 or more minutes late at destination; were cancelled; did not complete their full journey; or failed to stop at a station)</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-03-12T15:41:33.35Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856040/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856040/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856040/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-03-06","Southeastern: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what proportion  of trains on the Southeastern rail network have been delayed in each of the past five years; and what proportion of those delayed trains were the fault of (a) Southeastern and (b) Network Rail.","false","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett","131206"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856041","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-12","<p>The role that allied health professionals and other clinicians play in National Health Service leadership is of utmost importance and we engage with a range of professions to understand how best to support clinical leaders. My hon. Friend, the former Minister of State (Mr Phillip Dunne MP), met the Allied Health Professionals Federation on 29 November 2017.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-03-12T15:03:55.377Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856041/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856041/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856041/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-06","Health Professions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, pursuant to the Answer of 11 September 2017 to Question 9019, what plans he has to meet with the Allied Health Professionals Federation on allied health professionals in leadership roles in the NHS.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","131207"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856042","Home Office","false","2018-03-13","<p>Under section 67 of the Immigration Act 2016 (‘Dubs Amendment’), the Government has invited referrals of eligible children from France, Greece and Italy. In line with our published policy statement, each child will have an individual Best Interests Determination. It is the responsibility of participating States to refer eligible children. <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/policy-statement-section-67-of-the-immigration-act-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/policy-statement-section-67-of-the-immigration-act-2016</a>.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-03-13T17:51:22.703Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856042/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856042/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856042/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-03-06","Refugees: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what her policy is on the resettlement of disabled refugees under the Dubs scheme.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","131208"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856043","Treasury","false","2018-03-13","<p>The Chancellor has not had any recent discussions with the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions about marginal tax rates.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2018-03-13T13:15:02.167Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856043/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856043/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856043/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-03-06","Marginal Tax Rates","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions on the marginal tax rates applying to (a) men and (b) women at different income levels.","false","Biography information for Anneliese Dodds","Oxford East","Anneliese Dodds","131209"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856044","Home Office","false","2018-03-12","<p>The Home Office does not centrally hold the information requested.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2018-03-12T17:06:42.497Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856044/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856044/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856044/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-03-06","Police: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what proportion of police officers in each police force have completed mandatory mental health training.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","131210"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856045","Women and Equalities","false","2018-03-14","<p>The Equality and Human Rights Commission is currently undertaking a review of its guidance on the Public Sector Equality Duty for public authorities in England and non-devolved bodies in Scotland and Wales. The revised guidance will be published on the Commission's website in the summer.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-03-14T17:50:39.407Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856045/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856045/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856045/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2018-03-06","Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, what the timetable is of the publication  of the updated Advisory Statement on implementing the Equality Duty by the Equalities and Human Rights Commission.","false","Biography information for Anneliese Dodds","Oxford East","Anneliese Dodds","131211"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856046","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-03-14","<p>Details of ministerial and permanent secretary meetings with external organisations on departmental business are published on a quarterly basis at <a href="http://www.gov.uk/" target="_blank">www.gov.uk</a>.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-03-14T13:08:40.243Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856046/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856046/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856046/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-03-06","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: Appleby","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, whether  (a) he, (b) Ministers of his Department and (c) officials in his Department have held meetings with the legal firm Appleby's since October 2017.","false","Biography information for Anneliese Dodds","Oxford East","Anneliese Dodds","131212"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856047","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-03-23","<p>The Department has devolved the administration of local council tax support schemes to local authorities in order to enable them to best meet the needs of their local communities. Local authorities are required to consult local residents when designing their schemes and to take their views into account.</p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Rishi Sunak",,"2018-03-23T16:19:27.127Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856047/answer","Biography information for Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856047/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856047/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-03-06","Council Tax: Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the effect of the reduction in the availability of full council tax relief for working-age people on (a) household poverty and (b) child poverty.","false","Biography information for Anneliese Dodds","Oxford East","Anneliese Dodds","131213"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856048","Cabinet Office","false","2018-03-12","<p>There are no grounds for rejecting a vote on the basis that the vote was cast by a voter who had dementia and therefore, the Government does not hold any data relevant to this question. It is not possible to determine whether a vote has been cast by a voter with dementia.</p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith",,"2018-03-12T17:56:56.16Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856048/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856048/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856048/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-03-06","General Elections: Dementia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many votes cast (a) in person, (b) by proxy and (c) by postal vote were declared void due to the voter being judged to suffer from dementia in each of the last four general elections.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","131214"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856049","Treasury","false","2018-03-14","<p>The Government keeps all taxes and tax reliefs under review.</p><p> </p><p>In 2017 HMRC set up a Working Group with the charity sector to improve people’s understanding of Gift Aid and to review any areas of the process that can be improved. One of the issues that has come up as part of that working group is the question of whether charity shops could stop sending letters to their donors if the goods that have been donated have been sold for less than a certain amount, for example £20.</p><p> </p><p>The working group is continuing to explore all options, and officials are meeting with members of the working group to discuss this specific issue in April.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick","131216 ; 131217","2018-03-14T16:22:39.567Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856049/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856049/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856049/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-03-06","Gift Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of introducing a de minimis limit of £20 on retail Gift Aid claims for shops in the charity retail sector on that sector.","false","Biography information for Anneliese Dodds","Oxford East","Anneliese Dodds","131215"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856050","Treasury","false","2018-03-14","<p>The Government keeps all taxes and tax reliefs under review.</p><p> </p><p>In 2017 HMRC set up a Working Group with the charity sector to improve people’s understanding of Gift Aid and to review any areas of the process that can be improved. One of the issues that has come up as part of that working group is the question of whether charity shops could stop sending letters to their donors if the goods that have been donated have been sold for less than a certain amount, for example £20.</p><p> </p><p>The working group is continuing to explore all options, and officials are meeting with members of the working group to discuss this specific issue in April.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick","131215 ; 131217","2018-03-14T16:22:39.63Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856050/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856050/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856050/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-03-06","Gift Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what representations he has received (a) in support of and (b) opposed to the introduction of a de minimis limit of £20 on retail Gift Aid claims for shops in the charity retail sector.","false","Biography information for Anneliese Dodds","Oxford East","Anneliese Dodds","131216"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856051","Treasury","false","2018-03-14","<p>The Government keeps all taxes and tax reliefs under review.</p><p> </p><p>In 2017 HMRC set up a Working Group with the charity sector to improve people’s understanding of Gift Aid and to review any areas of the process that can be improved. One of the issues that has come up as part of that working group is the question of whether charity shops could stop sending letters to their donors if the goods that have been donated have been sold for less than a certain amount, for example £20.</p><p> </p><p>The working group is continuing to explore all options, and officials are meeting with members of the working group to discuss this specific issue in April.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick","131215 ; 131216","2018-03-14T16:22:39.693Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856051/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856051/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856051/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-03-06","Gift Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether he plans to introduce a de minimis limit of £20 on retail Gift Aid claims for shops in the charity retail sector.","false","Biography information for Anneliese Dodds","Oxford East","Anneliese Dodds","131217"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856052","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-03-12","<p>Total US imports of steel from the UK in 2017 were 351 thousand tonnes with a value of £360m. This represents 5% of UK steel production in 2017 in tonnage. We are working closely with the steel and aluminium industries to assess the potential impact of these measures.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2018-03-12T14:27:20.593Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856052/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856052/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856052/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-03-06","Iron and Steel: USA","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment his Department has made of the effect on the UK steel industry of the proposed introduction of steel tariffs by President Trump.","false","Biography information for Gill Furniss","Sheffield, Brightside and Hillsborough","Gill Furniss","131218"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856053","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-03-12","<p>The Voluntary Right to Buy Midlands pilot will give thousands more housing association tenants the opportunity to enjoy the benefits of home ownership. The Government is currently engaging with the National Housing Federation and housing associations in the Midlands, and more details on the pilot will be announced in due course.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2018-03-12T11:55:31.547Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856053/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856053/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856053/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-03-06","Right to Buy Scheme: Stafford","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, if he will publish the housing associations in Stafford constituency that are eligible for the regional pilot of the Right to Buy for housing association tenants.","false","Biography information for Jeremy Lefroy","Stafford","Jeremy Lefroy","131219"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856054","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-03-12","<p>The Department for Work and Pensions does not hold or collect data on the sector of the economy that its claimants have worked in or currently work in.</p><p> </p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-03-12T12:26:48.523Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856054/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856054/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856054/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-03-06","Social Security Benefits: Agriculture","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what recent assessment she has made of trends in the levels of benefit claims made by people who work in the agricultural sector.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","131220"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856055","Treasury","false","2018-03-14","<p>The government has committed to create a United Kingdom Shared Prosperity Fund following Brexit. The fund will support all regions across the four nations of the UK to achieve sustainable, inclusive growth, based on our modern industrial strategy. Further details on the fund will be set out in due course.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2018-03-14T12:23:17.973Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856055/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856055/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856055/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-03-06","EU Grants and Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether it is his policy for the UK Shared Prosperity Fund to be available to managing authorities in all parts of the UK.","false","Biography information for Luke Graham","Ochil and South Perthshire","Luke Graham","131221"
